Units.5: Precharge Done Based On 10 Second Limit

0x075.Description: Time (in seconds) that the flag/PTT buttons have been pressed. Interval is the minimum message send rate when neither button is pressed.

0x07B.Description: info about how the wheel is configured

0x0A1.Description: Telemetry errors, message is sent when an error occurs

0x0A2.Description: Telemetry warnings, sent when a warning occurs

0x0B1.Description: datalogger errors, message is sent when an error occurs

0x0B2.Description: DataLogger warnings, sent when a warning occurs

0x0B3.Description: Voltage Monitoring from DataLogger, rolling average of ~0.5s

0x100.Description: Bitmap indicating which lights the chase car board is enabling on. 1 means turn on, 0 means ignore this light.

0x101.Description: Bitmap indicating which lights the chase car board is turning off. 1 means turn off, 0 means ignore this light.

0x102.Description: Message to manually set minimum fan percent

0x103.Description: Message to manually set energy total

0x170.Description: Change the Configuration of the wheel. First Bitmap indicates which are being changed and second indicates what to change them to.

0x233.Description: Min, max, and average temperatures of battery pack

0x234.Description: Min, max, and average voltages of battery pack

0x250.Description: drive direction (FNR) and brake sensor state (pressed/unpressed)

0x251.Description: Bitmap indicating coast, cruise enable, and regen/accel. The RPM is from cruise control and Torque is from encoder

0x262.Description: Bitmap indicating manual control of power systems

0x301.Description: Turn signal and horn states. The interval is the minimum message send rate (the message is also sent if a horn/TS button is pressed/released)

0x400.Description: Bitmap. In general, 1 means on/pressed, 0 means off/unpressed. For 'Reverse Camera Button Enabled', 1/0 indicates whether button has toggled camera on/off

0x401.Description: Bitmap - raw output of non-flashing LEDs

0x402.Description: Bitmap - raw output of flashing LEDs

ValueNames: Pack power in, Pack energy in

0x440.Description: Information about precharge readings and state

0x460.Description: Status of the motor controller potentiometers

0x461.Description: Status of the motor controller potentiometers

0x462.Description: Status of the motor controller inputs

0x463.Description: Status of the motor controller inputs

0x472.Description: Reports one LED driver open/short circuit error with the device index and LED bitmap (see datasheet) indicating which driver LED outputs have errors. The device with index 0 is the one furthest on the bus. For the bitmap, a 1 indicates an error while 0 indicates normal functioning.

0x486.Description: Energy used by motor controller since start

0x487.Description: Energy used by motor controller since start

0x4A0.Description: the number of messages sent and received since start up

0x4A1.Description: performance statistics of the telemetry board

0x700.Description: Needed to find the motor controller on the network if the base address is lost or mis-configured.

ValueNames: Peak Imaginary Phase to Neutral Voltage

0x717.Description: Slip speed when driving induction motor

0xF01.Description: Calculated value. Grouping the current of each neutrino.

0xF02.Description: Calculated value. Grouping the voltage of each neutrino.

0xF03.Description: Calculated value. Calculating the power of each neutrino.

0xF06.Description: Calculated value. Estimated based off RPM and time

0xF07.Description: Calculated value. Estimated based off RPM

0xF08.Description: Calculated value. Estimated pack state of charge

0xF10.Description: Calculated value. Estimated based off RPM

0xF11.Description: Calculated value, power of the battery pack

0xF12.Description: Calculated value. Rough estimation of State of charge based linear cell voltage with 3.2 V as 0

0xF13.Description: Calculated value. The real voltage estimate accounts for the voltage drop due to the internal resistance. The real voltage should be a stable value that better indicates SOC
